SEED_DRY_RUN_DISPOSITION=non_mutating_cli_evidence_only
# Notes:
# This dry-run proves CLI argument parsing, tenant definition loading, and
# safety-gate enforcement only. It does NOT prove live synthetic traffic
# mutation, usage_records attribution, or staging state changes.
# DRY_RUN defaults to "true" at scripts/launch/seed_synthetic_traffic.sh:69;
# preflight_env() is only called when DRY_RUN != "true" (line 1499), and
# run_tenant() returns early with "[dry-run] skipping mutations" when
# DRY_RUN=true (line 1460), so the dry-run path requires no AWS/DB auth.
# See docs/launch/synthetic_traffic_seeder_plan.md for the remaining
# live-proof seam that a follow-up execute-mode session would have to close.
